<item>
<title><![CDATA[PLUMBERS read below….I had to cut the part of the video where ...]]></title>
<link>https://prank-arum.github.io/Feeds/TikTok/southernadventures1/7538541105420307743.mp4</link>
<guid>https://tiktok.com/embed/7538541105420307743</guid>
<description>
<![CDATA[<a href="https://tiktok.com/@southernadventures1/video/7538541105420307743">Full post</a> <a href="https://tiktok.com/embed/7538541105420307743">Embed</a><p><img src="https://p16-pu-sign-useast8.tiktokcdn-us.com/tos-useast8-p-0068-tx2/ooEIVQjqAAcfEv4ZVFfRkoDCoAn7UECYlACtA8~tplv-tiktokx-origin.image?dr=9636&amp;x-expires=1756512000&amp;x-signature=EVPthxw99gTEMErJcDLm2wKtr68%3D&amp;t=4d5b0474&amp;ps=13740610&amp;shp=b59d6b55&amp;shcp=43f4a2f9&amp;idc=useast8" /><br>PLUMBERS read below….I had to cut the part of the video where I talked about the UV filter to keep it under 90 seconds but here’s the situation: I have a UV Filter, but theres 2 problems with it. Firstly, for every 3 hours of non use, it’s gonna heat the water in the UV chamber to 140 degrees when tis not being used. So when you turn on the cold water at the bathroom sink you’re gonna get 140 degree water thats gonna burn. With it being a small space the water isn’t gonna have time to cool Secondly, it runs 24/7, which means it’s gonna use over 260KWH/Year, and thats a lot when youre on solar. It’s like a constant leach. Both those problems could be overcome by installing a flow switch, and allowing the UV filter to only run when its needed, but it takes 2-3 minutes for the bulb to heat up to a point where its effective. So essentially every time you go to get a drink from the fridge or sink it’s basically useless. Im not sure that I even need it, I’ve tested the well water on another (MUCH OLDER MUCH MORE SHALLOW) well about 200 yards from the one that is supplying the treehouse and there was no bad bacteria. This well is over 300 feet deep. Let me know thoughts please, THANKS! #<br>#treehouse
#fyppppppppppppppppppppppp
#foryoupage
#build
#construction
#plumbing
#offgrid]]>
</description>
